a chinese cargo ship of unknown origin sank over the weekend while in tow after being discovered in the southern gulf of thailand off the coast of nakhon si thammarat province the jin shui yuan 2 vessel was discovered abandoned and adrift near an offshore chevron oil rig last thursday 6 jan some 100 nautical miles from shores of songkhla province chevron staffers informed local authorities who then relayed the information to the 2nd naval area command based in songkhla an unmanned aerial vehicle uav drone was then deployed to survey the area after which the 2nd naval area command in cooperation with the thai maritime enforcement command centre thai mecc region 2 attempted to tow the vessel to shore at the tapi river mouth in surat thani s muang district the ship had apparently suffered severe damage with much of its equipment malfunctioning and all documents pertaining to its origins missing the operation soon encountered strong winds that caused the vessel to take on water and sink around 28 nautical miles from the shore of sichon district according to rear adm surasak prathanworapanya deputy director of thai mecc efforts are currently underway to clean oil leakage from the cargo ship and prevent it from approaching popular tourist destinations the vessel is not believed to have been the victim of piracy thailand china cargoship ghostship oil uav royalthainavy thainavy chevron gulfofthailand ประเทศไทย จ น เร อบรรท กส นค า เชฟรอน อ าวไทย

cobosocialart surrounded by universes is the title of an ongoing double exhibition of polish visual artist alicjakwade by pacegallery and koeniggalerie in seoul as her first solo exhibition in the south korean capital kwade presents more than 30 sculptures and works on paper that continue her exploration of the processes by which we perceive and construct reality entropie a new series of works on paper depicts the repetitive and rhythmic waves of watch hands showing just how arbitrary and coincidental the division of time into hours and minutes ultimately is and how starkly this settlement determines our experience of reality through our senses kwade s works reveal the limits of our perceptions and reminds us that we will always be a part of the system that we are trying to observe images alicja kwade surrounded by universes photos by sang tae kim courtesy of königseoul and pacegallery cobosocial alicjakwade sculptures soloexhibition galleryshows seoul

cobosocialart currently on view at massimodecarlogallery s hong kong outpost a stapled glass brings together seven new paintings by nashville based artist shannon cartier lucy zollieoo in her first exhibition in asia cartier lucy s paintings feature familiar subjects in absurd and cinematic settings a woman with her hands tied up by red strings a finger pointing into a dark void a filled glass of water with a stapled crack while these works don t explicitly depict particularly dark episodes they nevertheless exude an uncanny tension that could be associated with anxiety discomfort and irony as if her paintings are the prelude to endless narratives representing incredibly little while suggesting so much the exhibition runs until 10 january images all oil on canvases courtesy of massimodecarlogallery hong kong 1 2021 2 2021 3 2021 4 2021 5 2021 6 2021 cobosocial oiloncanvas contemporaryart shannoncartierlucy astapledglass hongkonggalleries hongkongexhibition

cobosocialdesign located in yunan western china the recently opened dongfengyun hotel mi le sits seamlessly amongst the poetic scenery of its surrounding nature the hotel is located within dongfengyun art town a village designed and built entirely by local artist luo xu housed in a series of curving structures built from locally fired red bricks the interior design of the hotel was helmed by hong kong based studio cheng_chung_design embracing the unique architectural design the studio blended natural materials with a muted colour palette and soft lighting to create a tranquil inviting ambience a good use of lighting both natural and artificial plays a huge part in the design of the hotel s interior a dramatic bowl shaped volume with a carved out skylight forms the entrance inside humble materials such as rammed earth and clay tiles are paired with natural stone flooring and high end furniture in a symbiosis of natural elements and architectural space images courtesy of chengchungdesign cobosocial architecture brickstructure design architectureinchina architexture

cobosocialart more than three years in the making british sculptor alexchinneck has unveiled a dramatic spiral staircase that occupies the full height of a red brick building in brighton this 25 metre four tonne sculptural walkway is made of galvanised steel and follows the form of a helical staircase at the base but uncoils upwards and springs into a trio of steel ribbons that hangs across the building s façade whimsicality is a recurring theme in chinneck s works known for his contextually responsive interventions he animates mundane urban landscapes with creations that fuse art architecture theatre and engineering he has previously been commissioned to create flagship projects for london design festival l_d_f_official and milan design week isaloniofficial images photos by marcwilmot courtesy and alex chinneck 1 5 installation views 2021 brighton uk 6 9 making of at millimetremakes cobosocial publicart sculpture design architecture urbanlandscape urbandesign publicintervention brighton

cobosocialfashion in the dior autumn winter 2022 men s show presented last december creative director mrkimjones pays tribute to the creativity of the beat generation in a setup inspired by jack kerouac s renowned novel published in 1957 the same year christian dior died channeling major beatnik vibes models in tweed jackets and trucker jackets paired with clashing socks and hiking boots reminiscent of the youth driven counterculture of 1950s america strutted down the custom catwalk which was designed as an 80 metre scroll covered with text from the novel the music was punctuated with passages from read by long time house ambassador robert pattinson while jones is known widely as a bibliophile the collection s focus on literature marks a new direction for him whose previous collections have typically featured collaborations with contemporary names such as peter doig shawn stussy and travis scott images and video courtesy of dior cobosocial kimjones olympialondon jackkerouac diormenfall fashionshow runway mensfashion
